ğŸŒ Project Overview

NewsHub is a dynamic and fully responsive news web application that allows users to explore the latest global headlines from trusted news sources in real-time.
Powered by the News API, this application fetches and displays breaking news, top stories, and user-searched articles in a visually appealing layout.

The goal of this project is to demonstrate API integration, frontend design, and backend interaction using modern web development technologies such as HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and PHP.

âœ¨ Key Features

âœ… Fetches real-time news articles from News API
âœ… Search functionality to find news by topic or keyword (e.g., â€œInternational Newsâ€)
âœ… Displays title, description, image, and link for each article
âœ… Beautiful, responsive UI designed using Bootstrap and CSS
âœ… Dynamic content loading using JavaScript fetch requests
âœ… Backend integration (PHP) for improved data handling and security
âœ… Error handling for failed API requests or empty results
âœ… Compatible with all modern browsers and screen sizes

